Reasoning: The paper discusses the issue of software citation and reference in scientific research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as it directly deals with software development and attribution. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries) are also relevant as they involve the use and management of software in research. cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) are less likely but still relevant as they deal with software design and evaluation from different perspectives.
